---

This project links against the proprietary Simulated Reality / LeiaSR SDK,
which is distributed under its own license (see the SDK's "Notices, Terms &
Conditions"). The SR runtime must be installed separately; the SDK is not
redistributed under the MIT terms above.

Bundled third-party components (all permissive / MIT-compatible):
  - Dear ImGui (third_party/imgui) : MIT License (Omar Cornut). The control
    panel is built with it; see third_party/imgui/LICENSE.txt.
  - Inter font (assets/fonts, embedded into the executable as a resource) :
    SIL Open Font License 1.1 (The Inter Project Authors); see
    assets/fonts/Inter-OFL.txt.
  - third_party/stb_image.h : public domain / MIT (Sean Barrett), used for
    image loading.
  - third_party/one_euro_filter.h : "1 Euro Filter" -- speed-adaptive
    low-pass filter by Gery Casiez, Nicolas Roussel, Daniel Vogel
    (CHI 2012). Original BSD 3-Clause License (Casiez/Roussel 2019).
    Used in the VR head-tracked viewer and the OpenTrack pipeline.
  - SR OpenTrack Bridge (https://github.com/effcol/leia-track-app-XYZ) :
    MIT License. The OpenTrack UDP sender (third_party/opentrack_udp.h)
    and the head-pose -> OneEuro -> OpenTrack mapping pipeline
    (third_party/opentrack_pipeline.h, src/OpenTrackBridge.{h,cpp}) are
    ported from this project.
  - NPClient.dll (TrackIR consumer API) : MIT License. Original author
    "uglyDwarf" via the Linuxtrack project
    (https://github.com/uglyDwarf/linuxtrack), subsequently maintained
    in OpenTrack's contrib/npclient
    (https://github.com/opentrack/opentrack). Vendored verbatim into
    third_party/npclient/npclient.c (apart from an added attribution
    header), built as a free-standing Windows DLL by CMake and embedded
    into SRLoom.exe as RCDATA. Extracted at first launch to
    %LOCALAPPDATA%\SRLoom\NPClient\ so TrackIR-compatible games can
    load it without users installing OpenTrack separately.

Attribution:
  - The HDMI 1.4 frame-packing decode in src/Converter.cpp was informed by
    "3DToElse" / "3DToElse_NTM3D.fx" by Jose Negrete (AKA BlueSkyDefender) with
    modifications by NTM3D, which is licensed under the Creative Commons
    Attribution 3.0 Unported License (CC BY 3.0,
    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/). The decode here is an
    independent re-implementation; this attribution is provided with thanks.
